The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a generalization of the Set Cover problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem is motivated by geometric set systems, which suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses LP relaxations and submodularity, which are topics in optimization and game theory (cs.GT). Information theory (cs.IT) is mentioned in the context of the sparse setting. Finally, the paper proposes improvements to previous work, which suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
